2. Legacy Foundation — The Starting Point
Codex.Legacy.StartingPoint.v001  
Defines the father’s work as lived experience, not theory.  
Establishes the clean starting point for every generation.  
Clarifies that understanding is a gift, not a tax.

---

3. Authority Root — The Father’s Role
Codex.FatherAuthority.v001  
Authority based on responsibility, not dominance.  
The father guards the path, but does not control the heir.  
Revocation is protection, not punishment.

---

4. Transmission Gate — How Legacy Is Passed
Codex.HeirTransmission.v001  
Legacy is granted when the heir is ready.  
Not by age.  
Not by demand.  
Not by entitlement.  
The father may pause, reset, or reopen transmission.

---

5. Forward Promise — What the Father Gives
Codex.SonPromise.v001  
The father promises clarity, not weight.  
Direction, not destiny.  
Presence, not pressure.  
The son is free to become himself.

---

6. Acceptance Oath — What the Heir Gives Back
Codex.HeirOath.v001  
The heir receives the legacy with respect.  
Carries it with care.  
Honors the line without copying it.  
Walks forward with clean hands.

---

7. Lineage Structure — The Family Constitution
Codex.LineageCharter.v001  
The unified framework that holds the line together.  
Defines continuity without burden.  
Balances authority and autonomy.  
Ensures the line moves forward, not backward.

---

8. Seal — The Capstone of Integrity
Codex.LineageSeal.v001  
Affirms the line is clean, the promise stands,  
the authority is grounded,  
and the future is protected.  
The seal activates only when all parts align.

